commit.message: dbgrpt_connector_states(): make more robust vs invalid data

add function ddc_set_verified_vcp_value_with_retry()

- wraps ddc_set_vcp_value()
- intended to perform retry if verification enabled
- controlled by global max_setvcp_verify_retries, option --i5

report user defined features as part of parsed capabilities

also convert tracing from DBGMSF() -> DBGTRC_...()
add init_dyn_parsed_capabilities()

fix segfault in dbgrpt_connector_state()

reported in issue #390
Emit "Executing options only" at start of noop command, not end

replace all_sysfs_i2c_info_drm() -> check_all_video_adapters_implement_drm()

all_sysfs_i2c_info_drm() fails for nvidia driver
move drm_connector_states.c/h from util to base

Add --discard-sleep-cache  as alt to --discard cache dsa|sleep

alias --discard-dsa-cache
for symmetry with --enable-dynamic-sleep, --disable-dynamic-sleep

Add option --discard-capabilities-cache as alt to --discard-cache capabilities

For symmetry with --enable-capabilities-cache, --disable-capabilities-cache
Add command "noop" (alias "iefbr14") just to report the effect of options

maintain connector number in Sys_Drm_Connector

new function:
- find_sys_crm_connector_by_connector_identifier()
- find_sys_drm_connector_by_connector_identifier()
